  "body": "### Version Information\r\n--\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe example contract at:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/master/examples/tokens/ERC20.vy\r\nIn line 74.\r\n\r\nNo checks are performed in the `transferFrom()` function.\r\nI am not sure but couldn't anyone just pass any `from/to` address combination and effectively steal their funds?\r\nDoesn't there need to be some check if the `_from` account has authorized the sender?\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nOption 1: Add something like this: \r\n`assert _from == msg.sender`\r\n\r\nOption 2: Make the function `@private`\r\n\r\nOption 3: Add something like this:\r\n`assert self.allowances[_to][msg.sender] >= _value`\r\n`self.allowances[_to][msg.sender] -= _value`\r\n\r\nOption 4: Both option 1 and option 2\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10925195/52504900-1c616f80-2bea-11e9-8551-b68369d7615d.png)\r\n\r\n",
